Introduction to the Modular Construction Market
Modular construction is a modern building approach where structures are prefabricated in controlled environments and then transported to the site for assembly. This method improves efficiency, reduces construction time, and minimizes waste, making it a preferred choice in residential, commercial, and industrial sectors. As sustainability and cost-effectiveness become critical in the construction industry, modular construction is gaining significant traction worldwide.
